history.content:
CS188 is set up to allow time conflicts and you only need one of the two courses to provide this permission. 

If, however, you aren't able to be enrolled for another reason (like in this instance that E27 is full and there is no space for anyone to be enrolled), then you get the error message you share above.  It's a little confusing.

"The enrollment system WILL ALLOW time conflicts between CompSci classes and other classes", however when I try to enroll in CS 188 and E 27,  CalCentral won't let me get off the waitlist for E 27 because "neither class allows time conflict enrollments". Am I misunderstanding the policy?
history.subject: Can't enroll in conflicting classes?
